olive oil
2 potato
1 packet coriander
2 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 tbs milk
½ cup plain flour
1 egg
¼ tsp salt
½ Pear
1 tsp vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Baby Leaves

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop coriander. Grate haloumi and carrot. Drain sweetcorn.

• In a medium bowl, combine carrot, sweetcorn, haloumi, coriander, garlic & herb seasoning, the milk, plain flour, the egg and the salt.
Season with pepper. Mix well to combine.

TIP: Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon, if it's too wet and doesn't hold its shape, add a little more flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of fritter mixture in batches and flatten with a spatula (3-4 per person).
• Cook fritters until golden, 3-4 minutes each side (don't flip too early!). Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.
TIP: Allow the fritters to set before you flip them.

• While the fritters are cooking, thinly slice pear (see ingredients) into wedges.
• In a second medium bowl, combine the vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add mixed salad leaves and pear and toss to coat.

• Divide halloumi and veggie fritters, roast potatoes and pear salad between plates. Enjoy!